article.headline: Oakland, Mich. 75, IUPUI 57
article.story: ROCHESTER, Mich. -- Erik Kangas scored 31 points to lead Oakland to a 75-57 Summit League victory over IUPUI on Thursday night. Kangas had a career-best 39 in Saturday's 93-88 victory at IPFW, and followed it up with a 20-point second half against the Jaguars. He hit 11 of 15 field goals, including eight of 11 3-pointers. He is now second on Oakland's career 3-point list with 287, five behind Jason Rozycki. Drew Maynard added 15 for Oakland (12-9, 5-3 Summit League), while Keith Benson had nine points and 10 rebounds. Freshman Alex Young led the Jaguars (9-10, 2-6) with 14 points, while Gary Patterson added 13 and Jon Avery had 12. The Golden Grizzlies had a 33-26 halftime advantage, and kept IUPUI at bay for most of the second half, thanks to seven 3-pointers. The Jaguars got as close as 57-51, but Kangas scored the next eight points to put the game away.
